    "en": {
      "title": "Anura reveals how oil gets into Anura's vehicle",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Janata Vimukthi Peramuna leader Mr. Anura Kumara Dissanayake stated that the party members get fuel from queues in the petrol stations for the vehicles of their party and they have never used the privileges of MPs to get fuel.",
        "He mentioned this in a press conference held today in Colombo. In a press conference held yesterday, Minister of Power and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera questioned how Mr. Anura Kumara Dissanayake will get oil when there is no oil in the country.",
        "He also said that when oil was given to parliamentarians from Narahenpitin, he refused both the occasions when he was asked to give oil from the parliament a few days ago.",
        "However, he said that in the last few days luxury vehicles had taken fuel from Kolonnawa Terminal.",
        "He also mentioned that Minister Kanchana Wijesekera should pay attention to those matters."
      ],
